d an extraordinary couple of days learning from and networking with the ROS community.  Attendees get tips and tricks from experts and meet and share ideas with fellow developers from around the globe.\n</p><p>\nPrevious editions of ROSCon include:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2013\" target=\"_blank\">May 2013: Stuttgart, Germany</a>\n<li><a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2012\" target=\"_blank\">May 2012: St. Paul, Minnesota</a>\n</ul>\n<p>\nThe usual format of ROSCon is a two-day program comprising technical talks and tutorials that introduce you to new tools and libraries, as well as teach you more about the ones you already know. The bulk of the program is 30-40 minute presentations.  There are also sessions of Lightning Talks, which are 3-minute mini-talks that are scheduled just-in-time at the conference.  And there’s open space at the conference for Birds-of-a-Feather meetings, impromptu hacking sessions, and informal presentations.\n</p><p>\nWe post videos of all the sessions after the conference (e.g., <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2013/?page_id=14\" target=\"_blank\">2013</a>, <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2012/?page_id=33\" target=\"_blank\">2012</a>).\n</p><p>\nWe usually hold ROSCon in May; look for a call for proposals in November or December, and please join us at the next ROSCon!\n</p>\";}s:6:\"84652f\";a:1:{s:13:\"pl_area_class\";s:21:\"side-navbar-separator\";}}s:5:\"draft\";a:7:{s:13:\"page-template\";s:12:\"rosotherpage\";s:10:\"custom-map\";a:1:{s:8:\"template\";a:1:{i:0;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"pl_area94dae8\";s:6:\"object\";s:13:\"PLSectionArea\";s:3:\"sid\";s:7:\"pl_area\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"94dae8\";s:7:\"content\";a:2:{i:0;a:7:{s:6:\"object\";s:8:\"PLColumn\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"84652f\";s:3:\"sid\";s:8:\"plcolumn\";s:4:\"span\";s:1:\"2\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:4:\"true\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:6:\"object\";s:19:\"PageLinesWidgetizer\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6: